<br>
I think in a multi guild alliance it can become very tough to enforce/maintain. It's also complicated and we should learn to walk before running.<br>
<br>
Right now a simple equation for loot should be is (item)  better/worse than (person) has? If (better) then person can roll.<br>
<br>
Later, when we get that simple thing worked out we can take people's comments and refine the system.<br>
<br>
I tend to favor the &quot;all roll&quot; mentality since that makes it easy for now. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzalliben.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zalliben</A> at: 5/8/01 10:29:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulandyalexandre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LandyAlexandre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 11:18:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=187.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loot Rules</span><hr size=1> I believe that rare items like planar BP's should go to the player(s) who have (just about) all the other pieces.  For although no individual is responsible for the raid as a whole, these players tend to be the ones we need the most in order to be in a plane in the first place.  <br>
<br>
Regardless of the looting rights the SGA ultimately decides to confer to me as a junior member of our planes crew, I pledge to do what i can to see that these items go to &quot;veterans.&quot;  I believe that this is the right decision, but i do not expect or ask others to hold the same opinion.  Whats more, if and when i grow to be a &quot;veteran&quot;, i will NOT ask or expect to have this &quot;privilege&quot; accorded to me.  <br>
<br>
The one thing i do ask is that we all continue to honor and respect each other's differences and strive together as a team.  If we do not, then our planar loot policies will be irrelevant for there will be no planar loot.  <br>
<br>
Landy Alexandre<br>
Spirit Guardians<br>
